with everything as the man of the house?

261
00:21:31,645 --> 00:21:32,646
Hey, Moon Mi-hui.

262
00:21:32,729 --> 00:21:36,566
I still have some fight left in me.
I'm not finished yet!

263
00:21:37,943 --> 00:21:38,944
Forget it.

264
00:21:39,903 --> 00:21:41,905
While we're at it, let's just end things.

265
00:21:42,572 --> 00:21:45,742
I'm sick and tired of living
so pathetically like this too.

266
00:21:45,826 --> 00:21:47,202
Sick and tired.

267
00:22:02,759 --> 00:22:05,804
Keep it down!

268
00:22:25,740 --> 00:22:29,411
<i>-Everything will be fine if I just die?</i>
<i>-</i>It keeps sticking.

269
00:22:31,746 --> 00:22:33,957
If I die,

270
00:22:35,750 --> 00:22:38,545
the world will change?

271
00:22:40,338 --> 00:22:43,091
<i>Think of it as paying</i>
<i>for your grandmother's sins.</i>

272
00:22:45,093 --> 00:22:46,261
Who are you?

273
00:22:46,344 --> 00:22:47,971
<i>In any case,</i>

274
00:22:48,472 --> 00:22:51,766
<i>you lived the past 20 years</i>
<i>thanks to your rich grandmother.</i>

275
00:22:51,850 --> 00:22:53,643
Are these

276
00:22:55,187 --> 00:22:57,105
my own thoughts?

277
00:22:58,148 --> 00:23:00,233
So if you can hear me, answer me.

278
00:23:01,651 --> 00:23:02,652
Tell me that you'll…

279
00:23:05,197 --> 00:23:06,281
die for us.

280
00:23:11,453 --> 00:23:13,371
For you…

281
00:23:14,623 --> 00:23:15,874
Die…

282
00:23:19,669 --> 00:23:20,504
gladly.

283
00:23:22,881 --> 00:23:24,424
Gladly…

284
00:23:37,729 --> 00:23:38,772
Die!

285
00:24:36,663 --> 00:24:38,540
I can't see anything.

286
00:24:38,623 --> 00:24:39,457
Seriously?

287
00:24:39,541 --> 00:24:42,502
-Just tell me how.
-Why are you wearing those?

288
00:24:42,586 --> 00:24:45,171
You can't see
because you're wearing these!

289
00:24:45,255 --> 00:24:46,881
That hurts!

290
00:24:46,965 --> 00:24:49,718
Hey, I'm not stupid.
I'm telling you, I can take these off.

291
00:24:49,801 --> 00:24:53,054
-For crying out loud.
-Just tell me to take them off.

292
00:24:59,102 --> 00:25:00,228
Is Eunie well?

293
00:25:00,854 --> 00:25:03,148
Tell her it's time to move back home,
if she can.

294
00:25:03,231 --> 00:25:05,275
She can stop being mad at me later.

295
00:25:05,358 --> 00:25:06,443
Sure.

296
00:25:06,943 --> 00:25:07,777
Sorry?

297
00:25:09,487 --> 00:25:10,655
Yes, ma'am.

298
00:25:12,866 --> 00:25:16,369
She's lost her mind.
Did she sleep at Master's house or what?

299
00:25:16,453 --> 00:25:18,830
I packed some food,
so take it and go home.

300
00:25:18,913 --> 00:25:20,332
She must be bored alone.

301
00:25:20,415 --> 00:25:21,249
I'll be back.

302
00:25:22,876 --> 00:25:24,169
See you later.

303
00:25:25,837 --> 00:25:26,921
Goodbye, ma'am.

304
00:25:28,423 --> 00:25:30,884
-What's going on?
-Did something happen?

305
00:25:30,967 --> 00:25:32,636
Auntie, I'm going out for a bit.

306
00:25:32,719 --> 00:25:33,928
Okay.

307
00:25:37,932 --> 00:25:39,517
You're completely fine.

308
00:25:40,185 --> 00:25:41,561
You didn't get kidnapped.

309
00:25:57,869 --> 00:26:01,081
I'll escort you home
after a hot cup of tea, Madam.

310
00:26:01,790 --> 00:26:05,835
I just need you to tell me where he is.
I really need to see him.

311
00:26:05,919 --> 00:26:08,129
He's overseas,
so you can't see him anyway.

312
00:26:08,213 --> 00:26:11,549
Overseas where? When is he coming back?
I can go to him instead.

313
00:26:11,633 --> 00:26:13,593
I'm not at liberty to disclose that.

314
00:26:16,096 --> 00:26:20,600
An overseas trip with a vague schedule
usually means a trip to the hospital.

315
00:26:22,644 --> 00:26:23,478
Where is he?

316
00:26:32,028 --> 00:26:33,738
It'd be best for you to leave now.

317
00:26:33,822 --> 00:26:35,198
Should I find out for myself?

318
00:26:42,163 --> 00:26:42,997
Yes, it's me.

319
00:26:43,498 --> 00:26:45,875
<i>I found out</i>
<i>who got Ha Won-do out on parole.</i>

320
00:26:50,004 --> 00:26:51,589
It was Chairman Nam Sun-gyu.

321
00:26:53,383 --> 00:26:55,552
He's at the Church
of Eternal Salvation now.

322
00:27:08,189 --> 00:27:10,775
Neither Master nor Chae-ni is answering.

323
00:27:12,777 --> 00:27:13,653
Mr. Son.

324
00:27:14,237 --> 00:27:17,323
Do you think they fell in love
and ran away together?

325
00:27:17,407 --> 00:27:19,159
This is your problem.

326
00:27:19,659 --> 00:27:22,287
That's seriously the genre you see
for those two?

327
00:27:22,787 --> 00:27:27,125
Don't you think a thriller or action film
with a deadly chase is far more likely?

328
00:27:28,668 --> 00:27:30,170
Or a kidnapping.

329
00:27:30,253 --> 00:27:32,338
But neither of them is answering.

330
00:27:32,422 --> 00:27:34,007
They could've spent the night--

331
00:27:34,090 --> 00:27:36,301
The truth is,
I saw Chae-ni being kidnapped.

332
00:27:39,345 --> 00:27:42,599
Turns out Oddball is in league
with the Church of Eternal Salvation.

333
00:27:43,516 --> 00:27:45,894
That jerk totally played us.

334
00:27:46,394 --> 00:27:48,855
There you go with your lying again.

335
00:27:56,279 --> 00:27:58,364
I am Kang Ro-bin.

336
00:28:03,119 --> 00:28:04,954
Oddball kidnapped Chae-ni.

337
00:28:05,580 --> 00:28:07,207
The Wunderkinder and the Church.

338
00:28:07,290 --> 00:28:10,084
He's in league with them
and kidnapped Chae-ni!

339
00:28:13,254 --> 00:28:15,340
What?! What do we do?

340
00:28:15,423 --> 00:28:16,841
What can we do?

341
00:28:17,842 --> 00:28:21,095
We hide.
Stay out of Oddball's sight for a while.

342
00:28:21,179 --> 00:28:23,890
But what about Chae-ni?
You said she was taken.

343
00:28:23,973 --> 00:28:26,518
What if they dissect her or something?

344
00:28:26,601 --> 00:28:27,602
What can we do?

345
00:28:28,228 --> 00:28:29,395
That's her damn fate.

346
00:28:30,980 --> 00:28:34,025
You can't say that, Mr. Son.

347
00:28:34,108 --> 00:28:36,903
We already abandoned Chae-ni once.
You want to do it again?

348
00:28:37,695 --> 00:28:40,073
Then what?
Are you going to fight them alone?

349
00:28:41,366 --> 00:28:42,242
Wait a minute.

350
00:28:43,910 --> 00:28:46,037
I'm going to see Master.
I'll ask him myself.

351
00:28:46,120 --> 00:28:48,122
Just sit down!

352
00:28:49,916 --> 00:28:52,252
You're not coming, are you?
Then I'll go alone.

353
00:28:52,335 --> 00:28:54,045
For heaven's sake.

354
00:28:54,128 --> 00:28:56,339
What could you do?
Are you trying to get killed?

355
00:28:56,422 --> 00:28:57,882
You're the biggest coward ever.

356
00:28:58,633 --> 00:29:01,386
What could you do
when you'd faint before ever saving her?

357
00:29:01,469 --> 00:29:03,054
How could you ever save anyone?

358
00:29:06,349 --> 00:29:08,101
Let go. That's way too hard.

359
00:29:08,726 --> 00:29:09,727
You're right.

360
00:29:10,228 --> 00:29:11,479
I'm a coward

361
00:29:12,063 --> 00:29:13,064
who's slow

362
00:29:13,773 --> 00:29:15,024
and tactless.

363
00:29:15,525 --> 00:29:18,903
Everyone in the world thinks
that I'm nothing but a nuisance.

364
00:29:21,322 --> 00:29:22,782
Everyone except Chae-ni.

365
00:29:24,033 --> 00:29:25,159
<i>Twenty-three!</i>

366
00:29:25,660 --> 00:29:27,036
Twenty-four!

367
00:29:27,537 --> 00:29:28,872
Twenty-five!

368
00:29:29,372 --> 00:29:30,707
Twenty-six!

369
00:29:30,790 --> 00:29:32,375
Twenty-seven!

370
00:29:32,876 --> 00:29:34,252
Twenty-eight!

371
00:29:34,752 --> 00:29:36,212
Twenty-nine!

372
00:29:36,796 --> 00:29:37,797
Thirty!

373
00:29:37,881 --> 00:29:38,965
Oh, come on!

374
00:29:39,549 --> 00:29:41,593
-What the heck?
-What's wrong with him?

375
00:29:42,844 --> 00:29:44,304
What are you doing?

376
00:29:44,387 --> 00:29:45,930
Is this that hard?

377
00:29:46,431 --> 00:29:47,724
Get a hold of yourselves!

378
00:29:47,807 --> 00:29:51,060
-Semester <i>just </i>started. Snap out of it!
-Hey, stop messing up.

379
00:29:52,812 --> 00:29:54,397
Next, 50 times! How many times?

380
00:29:54,480 --> 00:29:56,065
Fifty!

381
00:29:56,149 --> 00:29:57,525
Forty-three!

382
00:29:58,026 --> 00:29:59,193
Forty-four!

383
00:29:59,819 --> 00:30:01,070
Forty-five!

384
00:30:01,571 --> 00:30:02,989
Forty-six!

385
00:30:03,072 --> 00:30:04,365
Forty-seven!

386
00:30:05,491 --> 00:30:06,659
Forty-eight!

387
00:30:06,743 --> 00:30:07,827
Forty-nine!

388
00:30:08,661 --> 00:30:09,746
Fifty!

389
00:30:11,122 --> 00:30:12,081
Hey!

390
00:30:21,215 --> 00:30:22,675
Hey, Sap!

391
00:30:23,301 --> 00:30:24,969
How can you eat right now?

392
00:30:26,012 --> 00:30:27,847
Enjoy your meals, guys. I'm sorry.

393
00:30:29,891 --> 00:30:31,059
You idiot.

394
00:30:31,726 --> 00:30:33,603
-This looks good.
-Yeah, enjoy.

395
00:30:35,229 --> 00:30:36,522
Enjoy your meals.

396
00:30:38,733 --> 00:30:40,360
-Eat up.
-Hey, this is good.

397
00:30:56,960 --> 00:30:58,211
This fried egg is good.

398
00:31:00,129 --> 00:31:01,673
From now on,

399
00:31:02,256 --> 00:31:03,591
you eat lunch with me.

400
00:31:03,675 --> 00:31:05,635
What? Okay.

401
00:31:07,595 --> 00:31:10,723
Hey, Sappy Sap of Class 3. You idiot--

402
00:31:10,807 --> 00:31:11,933
Hey, don't.

403
00:31:12,016 --> 00:31:14,394
-Cut it out.
-I have something to tell you.

404
00:31:14,477 --> 00:31:16,229
Come on. Let's talk.

405
00:31:16,312 --> 00:31:18,356
-Let's go. It'll be quick.
-What is it?

406
00:31:23,403 --> 00:31:24,320
Let's eat.

407
00:31:41,087 --> 00:31:42,922
<i>That was the first time</i>

408
00:31:43,006 --> 00:31:44,382
<i>someone stood by me.</i>

409
00:31:44,966 --> 00:31:47,051
<i>Chae-ni was the first person</i>
<i>to do that for me.</i>

410
00:31:48,720 --> 00:31:50,388
I see, Ro-bin.

411
00:31:51,180 --> 00:31:53,641
But how about you let me go
for such long stories?

412
00:31:54,142 --> 00:31:57,520
It hurts so much. It hurts, okay?

413
00:32:00,898 --> 00:32:02,650
If you're going to hide, go ahead.

414
00:32:04,527 --> 00:32:06,029
Hey, at least eat before you go.

415
00:32:06,112 --> 00:32:08,948
Hey, Chae-ni's grandma
packed this for us. Ro-bin!

416
00:32:09,449 --> 00:32:10,408
Hey!

417
00:32:10,491 --> 00:32:12,452
What? A letter of resignation?

418
00:32:12,535 --> 00:32:15,121
Yeah, he says he's going back to Seoul.

419
00:32:15,621 --> 00:32:19,542
Just like this, out of nowhere,
without a goodbye or a farewell party?

420
00:32:19,625 --> 00:32:23,921
This is why I told you not to warm up
to those cold-hearted city boys, Na-yeong.

421
00:32:25,548 --> 00:32:26,799
Heartless bastard.

422
00:32:31,304 --> 00:32:32,597
You scared me.

423
00:32:36,601 --> 00:32:39,228
See? He never intended to stick around.

424
00:32:45,860 --> 00:32:47,570
That bastard.

425
00:32:51,949 --> 00:32:53,826
Whoa, why? What? Why?

426
00:32:53,910 --> 00:32:55,036
Sir?

427
00:32:56,079 --> 00:32:58,289
Is he really going back to Seoul?

428
00:32:58,998 --> 00:32:59,832
Yes.

429
00:33:00,333 --> 00:33:01,542
He is. Why do you ask?

430
00:33:07,298 --> 00:33:08,174
Did he see?

431
00:33:11,469 --> 00:33:13,387
PLEASE DISPOSE OF THIS

432
00:33:42,834 --> 00:33:43,835
Where's Chae-ni?

433
00:33:45,253 --> 00:33:47,088
Go home. I don't know anything.

434
00:33:56,222 --> 00:33:58,182
There you go, stomping away again!

435
00:33:58,766 --> 00:34:01,978
City Hall guy!
I swear I'll report you to the police!

436
00:34:02,728 --> 00:34:03,980
The truth is,

437
00:34:05,022 --> 00:34:07,316
I've felt strong since earlier.

438
00:34:07,984 --> 00:34:09,527
But I'm just so upset

439
00:34:11,279 --> 00:34:13,906
that I can't seem to lose my strength.

440
00:34:21,372 --> 00:34:23,541
Put me down and let's talk.

441
00:34:23,624 --> 00:34:25,334
Tell me where Chae-ni is first.

442
00:34:25,960 --> 00:34:27,128
What did you do to her?

443
00:34:27,753 --> 00:34:31,132
Master, did you really
hand her over to them?

444
00:34:31,215 --> 00:34:32,466
Did you

445
00:34:33,259 --> 00:34:35,553
really betray us?

446
00:35:39,742 --> 00:35:40,660
Hello?

447
00:35:40,743 --> 00:35:43,996
<i>Hey, Kang Ro-bin, where are you?</i>
<i>Did you go to see Oddball after all?</i>

448
00:35:44,080 --> 00:35:48,876
<i>The owner of Hearty House is going crazy</i>
<i>trying to find you and Chae-ni!</i>

449
00:35:52,797 --> 00:35:54,590
<i>I'm Eun Chae-ni's grandmother.</i>

450
00:36:09,188 --> 00:36:10,064
Go ahead.

451
00:36:10,564 --> 00:36:12,608
<i>I'd like to see you for a moment.</i>

452
00:36:13,818 --> 00:36:15,278
<i>Can you come over?</i>

453
00:36:15,778 --> 00:36:16,946
<i>You're okay, right?</i>

454
00:36:17,029 --> 00:36:19,198
<i>Please tell me you're okay!</i>

455
00:36:19,282 --> 00:36:20,366
<i>Hey! Hello?</i>

456
00:36:20,449 --> 00:36:21,450
Mr. Son.

457
00:36:21,534 --> 00:36:22,868
Please insult me.

458
00:36:22,952 --> 00:36:24,620
<i>Are you listening to me or not?</i>

459
00:36:25,121 --> 00:36:27,581
<i>I swear, you're dead meat when I find you!</i>

460
00:37:12,084 --> 00:37:13,753
EUN CHAE-NI'S BUCKET LIST

461
00:37:16,380 --> 00:37:18,591
1. CLIMB KILIMANJARO
2. SEE THE NORTHERN LIGHTS

462
00:37:18,674 --> 00:37:20,843
3. SEE THE HELLUSION
WHEN THEY COME TO KOREA

463
00:37:20,926 --> 00:37:22,595
AND EXPLORE SEOUL WHILE I'M THERE

464
00:37:22,678 --> 00:37:23,763
4. KISS

465
00:37:26,974 --> 00:37:29,018
5. EAT A WHOLE CAKE
6. RIDE THE EAGLE FORTRESS

466
00:37:32,730 --> 00:37:35,483
9. DATE
10. LIVE PAST 30

467
00:37:38,152 --> 00:37:40,780
LIVE PAST 30

468
00:37:42,281 --> 00:37:46,035
<i>Can I ask you something?</i>

469
00:37:49,372 --> 00:37:52,083
Is Master one of the people

470
00:37:53,292 --> 00:37:55,044
I'd be saving?

471
00:37:55,836 --> 00:37:57,630
Are you referring to 3972?

472
00:37:58,589 --> 00:37:59,715
If so,

473
00:38:00,424 --> 00:38:02,468
you've already saved him.

474
00:38:03,177 --> 00:38:04,762
In return for handing you over,

475
00:38:05,262 --> 00:38:06,847
he got to meet his mom.

476
00:38:15,481 --> 00:38:16,524
What?

477
00:38:18,192 --> 00:38:19,652
If that's the case…

478
00:38:21,654 --> 00:38:23,572
I can't even be mad at him.

479
00:38:28,536 --> 00:38:29,995
His mom?

480
00:38:30,079 --> 00:38:32,373
I can't beat that.

481
00:38:45,261 --> 00:38:47,847
All done. Come out here.

482
00:38:54,145 --> 00:38:56,313
I heard from Eunie

483
00:38:57,398 --> 00:38:58,649
that you're a Wunderkinder.

484
00:39:01,944 --> 00:39:02,778
I'm sorry.

485
00:39:04,947 --> 00:39:06,407
I asked you here

486
00:39:06,490 --> 00:39:09,535
because this may be
my last chance to apologize.

487
00:39:12,746 --> 00:39:14,039
I wanted to make sure

488
00:39:15,541 --> 00:39:17,960
you had a home-cooked meal before leaving.

489
00:39:22,923 --> 00:39:25,843
I know this won't make up for anything,

490
00:39:27,178 --> 00:39:29,472
but I thought it was the least I could do.

491
00:39:30,806 --> 00:39:32,266
As you said,

492
00:39:33,767 --> 00:39:36,270
I don't think a meal
can make up for all those years.

493
00:39:38,272 --> 00:39:39,440
I'll be on my way now.

494
00:39:39,523 --> 00:39:41,025
Where is my Chae-ni?

495
00:39:43,944 --> 00:39:45,362
That's all I ask.

496
00:39:46,238 --> 00:39:47,406
Did you, by any chance,

497
00:39:48,240 --> 00:39:50,451
hand her over to Ha Won-do?

498
00:39:52,828 --> 00:39:56,248
I'm not asking you to save her.
I'll do the saving.

499
00:39:56,999 --> 00:39:59,293
Just tell me where Chae-ni is.

500
00:40:00,169 --> 00:40:01,170
Where is she now?

501
00:40:03,964 --> 00:40:04,840
It might

502
00:40:06,258 --> 00:40:07,259
already be too late.

503
00:40:07,343 --> 00:40:08,260
No.

504
00:40:08,761 --> 00:40:10,221
I know she's hanging in there.

505
00:40:11,347 --> 00:40:15,184
My baby doesn't go down that easily.
I know because she's my baby.

506
00:40:22,650 --> 00:40:23,484
My apologies.

507
00:40:36,705 --> 00:40:38,666
So he actually came when she asked.

508
00:40:39,250 --> 00:40:40,334
That traitor.

509
00:40:41,585 --> 00:40:44,088
And I guess you came
when asked, too, Mr. Son.

510
00:40:44,588 --> 00:40:45,839
You said you'd be hiding.

511
00:40:47,132 --> 00:40:47,967
Hey.

512
00:40:52,721 --> 00:40:53,639
What's going on?

513
00:40:54,390 --> 00:40:56,642
Did he already have it out with her?

514
00:40:57,142 --> 00:40:58,561
He's not in bad shape at all.

515
00:40:58,644 --> 00:40:59,478
Master!

516
00:41:01,355 --> 00:41:02,856
Kang Ro-bin, stay out of it!

517
00:41:05,442 --> 00:41:07,945
Where are you going?
Are you going to save Chae-ni?

518
00:41:08,028 --> 00:41:09,905
I bet 10,000 won that he isn't.

519
00:41:09,989 --> 00:41:13,701
-Are you really not going to save her?
-I bet my honor that he definitely won't.

520
00:41:20,583 --> 00:41:23,210
<i>I thought it was all meaningless.</i>

521
00:41:31,844 --> 00:41:33,762
Is that the child?

522
00:41:34,346 --> 00:41:35,180
Yes.

523
00:41:39,518 --> 00:41:41,353
I see.

524
00:41:47,026 --> 00:41:51,238
<i>That it didn't matter to me</i>
<i>whatever happened to someone else's life.</i>

525
00:41:51,739 --> 00:41:53,032
Come on, Master!

526
00:41:53,115 --> 00:41:55,367
You're really gonna run for it,
aren't you?

527
00:42:02,833 --> 00:42:03,917
<i>Such annoying,</i>

528
00:42:05,294 --> 00:42:07,004
<i>bothersome people.</i>

529
00:42:08,797 --> 00:42:09,882
Mr. Oddball.

530
00:42:09,965 --> 00:42:12,760
<i>We get it, all right?</i>
<i>You're not exactly happy to see us.</i>

531
00:42:12,843 --> 00:42:13,886
This guy won't give up!

532
00:42:13,969 --> 00:42:15,512
<i>But we still like you, Master.</i>

533
00:42:16,597 --> 00:42:19,308
<i>Most people don't bother</i>
<i>if they don't want to help.</i>

534
00:42:19,391 --> 00:42:21,560
<i>But even if you don't want to,</i>

535
00:42:21,644 --> 00:42:23,270
<i>you help in the end.</i>

536
00:42:24,063 --> 00:42:24,980
<i>Know why?</i>

537
00:42:26,440 --> 00:42:27,983
Because you're on my side.

538
00:42:28,067 --> 00:42:29,860
<i>Master!</i>

539
00:42:30,402 --> 00:42:32,071
<i>No concept of personal space</i>

540
00:42:32,863 --> 00:42:35,074
<i>in the way they just keep barging in.</i>

541
00:42:41,705 --> 00:42:42,790
I wanted to find her.

542
00:42:46,168 --> 00:42:48,879
And I wanted to know
what it was that I'd lost.

543
00:42:53,300 --> 00:42:54,927
I thought that if I found my mom…

544
00:42:59,890 --> 00:43:01,767
I could turn my life around…

545
00:43:04,436 --> 00:43:06,230
even just a little bit.

546
00:43:15,197 --> 00:43:16,281
That's why.

547
00:43:19,451 --> 00:43:20,703
That's why I…

548
00:44:02,411 --> 00:44:04,288
<i>Such ridiculously…</i>

549
00:44:06,123 --> 00:44:07,332
<i>warm</i>

550
00:44:08,834 --> 00:44:10,252
<i>and friendly people.</i>

551
00:44:11,545 --> 00:44:12,379
Why? What?

552
00:44:12,880 --> 00:44:14,256
Did I tick you off?

553
00:44:21,889 --> 00:44:25,350
What, are you calling the Church?
To tell them to kidnap us too?

554
00:44:27,186 --> 00:44:28,437
I need people.

555
00:44:30,105 --> 00:44:30,981
How many?

556
00:44:31,064 --> 00:44:32,816
The more, the better.

557
00:44:33,317 --> 00:44:34,193
A hundred?

558
00:44:35,319 --> 00:44:36,779
No, make that 200.

559
00:44:39,907 --> 00:44:40,991
You got it.

560
00:44:44,787 --> 00:44:46,163
I'm sorry, Mr. Yang.

561
00:44:46,246 --> 00:44:47,539
Please, just this once.

562
00:44:47,623 --> 00:44:50,751
After you up and left as though you were
never going to see us again?

563
00:44:50,834 --> 00:44:53,962
Guess some people's antisocial tendencies
rubbed off on you.

564
00:44:54,046 --> 00:44:54,922
Anti…

565
00:44:55,005 --> 00:44:56,173
What?

566
00:45:03,889 --> 00:45:05,057
Please.

567
00:45:09,812 --> 00:45:10,979
PUBLIC HOUSING DEPARTMENT

568
00:45:12,856 --> 00:45:16,151
Victory! Get the job done!
Class 560, Yang Seok-u!

569
00:45:16,235 --> 00:45:17,069
Victory!

570
00:45:17,778 --> 00:45:19,530
-What is it?
-Some energy drinks, sir.

571
00:45:19,613 --> 00:45:20,447
Thanks, but--

572
00:45:20,531 --> 00:45:22,574
Allow me to just use your computer.

573
00:45:22,658 --> 00:45:24,743
"Church of…" Stop right there.

574
00:45:24,827 --> 00:45:26,954
You're poking the hornet's nest!
Take this back.

575
00:45:27,037 --> 00:45:29,289
How about some liquor?
Your favorite hard liquor.

576
00:45:29,373 --> 00:45:31,792
<i>-</i>Bomb shots?
-Yes, bomb shots, sir.

577
00:45:31,875 --> 00:45:34,253
-Well, that is…
-Okay, great.

578
00:45:34,837 --> 00:45:36,129
SWEET HOME WELFARE CENTER

579
00:45:36,213 --> 00:45:37,589
CHURCH OF ETERNAL SALVATION

580
00:45:37,673 --> 00:45:39,967
Floor plans
of the Church of Eternal Salvation.

581
00:45:41,760 --> 00:45:42,761
Thank you, Mr. Yang.

582
00:45:44,346 --> 00:45:45,806
So you even smile, huh?

583
00:45:45,889 --> 00:45:48,308
You finally seem human.

584
00:45:48,392 --> 00:45:50,060
I always figured

585
00:45:50,143 --> 00:45:53,605
you had a compartment on your back
to insert batteries or something.

586
00:45:59,069 --> 00:46:01,905
Actually, I'm… the rechargeable kind.

587
00:46:08,829 --> 00:46:10,080
220 volts.

588
00:46:22,718 --> 00:46:24,303
This area is too open.

589
00:46:25,429 --> 00:46:29,099
As for this side, it'll be hard
to secure a route to the drain.

590
00:46:36,064 --> 00:46:38,358
Let's just report it to the cops.

591
00:46:38,442 --> 00:46:41,111
This is beyond our scope.

592
00:46:41,194 --> 00:46:42,279
And what would we say?

593
00:46:43,488 --> 00:46:44,448
Goddammit.

594
00:46:45,032 --> 00:46:47,659
What else? We tell the truth,
whether they believe or not.

595
00:46:47,743 --> 00:46:50,495
Then we'll have done our part,
and we can walk away.

596
00:46:51,663 --> 00:46:53,040
They won't believe us anyway.

597
00:46:53,540 --> 00:46:56,668
The first thing those people do
is silence the police.

598
00:46:56,752 --> 00:46:58,712
All the more reason for us to stay put.

599
00:46:58,795 --> 00:47:01,423
If the police can't do anything about it,
what can we do?

600
00:47:01,506 --> 00:47:03,634
Who are you to get involved?

601
00:47:05,510 --> 00:47:06,803
Chae-ni is my friend!

602
00:47:07,930 --> 00:47:09,514
And I <i>will </i>save her.

603
00:47:11,308 --> 00:47:13,810
So you went from a toddler
to a 30-year-old muscle man,

604
00:47:13,894 --> 00:47:15,729
but what can you actually do?

605
00:47:15,812 --> 00:47:19,691
That superpower just about
puts you on par with other people now.

606
00:47:19,775 --> 00:47:21,944
So what could you possibly do?

607
00:47:22,027 --> 00:47:25,280
You seem to be under the delusion
that you've become something amazing,

608
00:47:25,864 --> 00:47:28,158
but compared to the Wunderkinder,
you're a rookie.

609
00:47:28,241 --> 00:47:29,952
If you value your life,

610
00:47:30,035 --> 00:47:32,788
just stay put and don't get involved.

611
00:47:32,871 --> 00:47:35,248
Even if you get involved,
there's nothing you--

612
00:47:45,342 --> 00:47:47,427
I guess there's a lot you could do.

613
00:47:50,806 --> 00:47:52,766
Now it's time to train in real life.

614
00:47:52,849 --> 00:47:54,476
How can we trust you?

615
00:47:55,268 --> 00:47:57,396
We never know
when you'll become Mr. Curveball.

616
00:47:57,479 --> 00:48:00,107
What if we all go in to save her,
and you change your mind?

617
00:48:00,190 --> 00:48:01,024
Yes, fine.

618
00:48:01,108 --> 00:48:04,611
I know the situation right now
is urgent and desperate,

619
00:48:05,112 --> 00:48:07,030
but should we risk our lives for her?

620
00:48:07,114 --> 00:48:10,951
Hey, Kang Ro-bin, say something.
This just isn't right.

621
00:48:11,034 --> 00:48:12,494
Back the fudge off.

622
00:48:13,662 --> 00:48:15,122
What's with the stink eye?

623
00:48:15,205 --> 00:48:18,083
When you, of all people,
look at me like that,

624
00:48:18,166 --> 00:48:20,961
it makes me feel so darn pathetic.

625
00:48:21,044 --> 00:48:23,839
You do seem pretty darn pathetic.

626
00:48:25,215 --> 00:48:27,551
Let's go, Master. Just us.

627
00:48:27,634 --> 00:48:28,468
Hey.

628
00:48:28,552 --> 00:48:31,179
Wait. Who said I wasn't going?

629
00:48:31,263 --> 00:48:32,514
Okay, fine.

630
00:48:33,640 --> 00:48:34,683
Got it. I'll go.

631
00:48:34,766 --> 00:48:36,059
I'm going.

632
00:48:36,560 --> 00:48:38,186
But on one condition.

633
00:48:41,189 --> 00:48:43,400
We file the police report in my name.

634
00:48:47,320 --> 00:48:48,155
Deal!

635
00:49:12,220 --> 00:49:13,096
HAESEONG CITY HALL

636
00:49:26,026 --> 00:49:27,444
<i>My code name will be</i>

637
00:49:27,944 --> 00:49:30,197
<i>"Condolence Wreath."</i>

638
00:49:31,281 --> 00:49:35,077
<i>Do you think we can get there</i>
<i>before they wrench out Chae-ni's heart?</i>

639
00:49:35,827 --> 00:49:36,745
<i>Enough chatter.</i>

640
00:49:37,245 --> 00:49:40,582
<i>Let's get moving. If we're too late,</i>
<i>this will all have been for nothing.</i>

641
00:49:46,755 --> 00:49:48,131
EUN CHAE-NI

642
00:50:40,851 --> 00:50:41,810
This is infuriating!

643
00:50:43,979 --> 00:50:45,856
What exactly is going on out there?

644
00:50:46,398 --> 00:50:49,401
Why are they keeping us in here
and not letting us go outside?

645
00:50:50,235 --> 00:50:51,444
Know anything, Ju-ran?

646
00:50:54,406 --> 00:50:56,324
I think Father found that child.

647
00:50:56,408 --> 00:50:57,701
That child?

648
00:50:59,161 --> 00:51:01,413
You mean the Child of Eternity?
He found him?

649
00:51:04,166 --> 00:51:06,126
Then why didn't he tell us?

650
00:51:06,209 --> 00:51:09,087
If he found him,
he should have called us first.

651
00:51:09,796 --> 00:51:11,298
Isn't this a bit odd?

652
00:51:11,381 --> 00:51:12,799
Don't you two agree?

653
00:51:12,883 --> 00:51:14,259
I'm sure he has a reason.

654
00:51:15,218 --> 00:51:16,052
Just wait.

655
00:51:18,054 --> 00:51:19,848
You know what Father hates most.

656
00:51:20,807 --> 00:51:22,267
Asking unnecessary questions.

657
00:51:28,690 --> 00:51:30,942
We could listen in another way.

658
00:51:36,156 --> 00:51:37,115
You don't mean…

659
00:51:37,699 --> 00:51:38,617
Are you insane?

660
00:51:45,916 --> 00:51:48,043
-Father.
-I'm busy now. Later.

661
00:51:48,126 --> 00:51:50,420
We heard you found the Child of Eternity.

662
00:51:56,635 --> 00:51:58,220
Please tell us.

663
00:51:59,304 --> 00:52:01,348
Why are you hiding that child from us?

664
00:52:01,431 --> 00:52:03,308
What exactly are you suspecting?

665
00:52:10,232 --> 00:52:11,691
<i>Tell us.</i>

666
00:52:12,734 --> 00:52:14,819
<i>What are you hiding from us?</i>

667
00:52:22,035 --> 00:52:23,370
<i>Answer me.</i>

668
00:52:25,580 --> 00:52:27,332
<i>Please answer me, Father.</i>

669
00:52:42,472 --> 00:52:43,723
"Now faith is

670
00:52:45,642 --> 00:52:47,894
confidence in what we hope for

671
00:52:48,395 --> 00:52:51,356
and assurance about what we do not see."

672
00:52:54,776 --> 00:52:56,236
If you do not have faith in me,

673
00:52:56,319 --> 00:53:00,323
you'll never be able to see
what you hope for, Ju-ran.

674
00:53:10,500 --> 00:53:13,837
You possess the ability
that I love most of all.

675
00:53:14,337 --> 00:53:17,257
It's also the ability I need the most.

676
00:53:17,841 --> 00:53:19,092
But that doesn't mean

677
00:53:20,051 --> 00:53:22,137
you can use it on me.

678
00:53:31,313 --> 00:53:33,064
Elder Yoon has been in touch.

679
00:53:33,148 --> 00:53:35,650
He says there is a crowd gathered
outside the building.

680
00:53:35,734 --> 00:53:38,069
Didn't you hear there's been a problem?

681
00:53:39,112 --> 00:53:39,946
You should go.

682
00:53:58,757 --> 00:54:01,593
You are my daughter of faith, Ju-ran.

683
00:54:03,386 --> 00:54:05,930
As you are my first child,

684
00:54:07,098 --> 00:54:09,351
I will save you before anyone else.

685
00:54:11,811 --> 00:54:12,937
So,

686
00:54:13,021 --> 00:54:15,357
do not test me.

687
00:54:16,941 --> 00:54:20,945
Doubt and distrust
will only rot your bones.

688
00:54:25,617 --> 00:54:26,451
Yes,

689
00:54:27,577 --> 00:54:28,411
Father.

690
00:54:44,219 --> 00:54:47,097
<i>Give us back our families!</i>

691
00:54:47,180 --> 00:54:49,849
Give them back!

692
00:54:49,933 --> 00:54:52,060
Cultists, begone!

693
00:54:52,143 --> 00:54:54,521
Begone!

694
00:54:54,604 --> 00:54:56,731
Give us back our families!

695
00:54:56,815 --> 00:54:58,775
Give them back!

696
00:54:58,858 --> 00:55:00,985
Cultists, begone!

697
00:55:01,069 --> 00:55:02,445
Begone!

698
00:55:02,529 --> 00:55:03,780
Please save them all.

699
00:55:03,863 --> 00:55:06,699
A criminal organization
that brainwashes people!

700
00:55:06,783 --> 00:55:07,951
Leave!

701
00:55:08,034 --> 00:55:09,786
Leave!

702
00:55:09,869 --> 00:55:12,288
-Please save them all.
-Give us back our families!

703
00:55:12,372 --> 00:55:14,791
Give them back!

704
00:55:14,874 --> 00:55:16,835
Cultists, begone!

705
00:55:16,918 --> 00:55:19,170
Begone!

706
00:55:19,254 --> 00:55:20,964
Give us back our families!

707
00:55:21,047 --> 00:55:22,590
Did you contact the police?

708
00:55:23,508 --> 00:55:24,342
Yes.

709
00:55:24,426 --> 00:55:26,010
They said they're on their way.

710
00:55:26,094 --> 00:55:28,304
Begone!

711
00:55:28,388 --> 00:55:30,890
Give us back our families!

712
00:55:30,974 --> 00:55:32,892
Give them back!

713
00:55:32,976 --> 00:55:36,354
-Cultists, begone!
-Begone!

714
00:55:36,438 --> 00:55:41,025
-Give us back our families!
-Give them back!

715
00:55:41,526 --> 00:55:44,320
The Church is a criminal organization
that brainwashes people!

716
00:55:44,404 --> 00:55:48,074
Leave!

717
00:55:48,158 --> 00:55:49,492
All right, everyone!

718
00:55:49,576 --> 00:55:53,288
Let's let them hear our screams, our fury!

719
00:56:24,235 --> 00:56:25,570
Thanks.

720
00:56:29,240 --> 00:56:30,533
I'm Number 4204.

721
00:56:35,246 --> 00:56:36,789
<i>Thanks to the fire that day,</i>

722
00:56:37,373 --> 00:56:39,584
I got out just before
they experimented on me.

723
00:56:40,877 --> 00:56:43,171
There were 20 other kids like me.

724
00:56:43,755 --> 00:56:44,714
Thanks to you,

725
00:56:45,507 --> 00:56:47,217
we're all okay and living our lives.

726
00:56:50,345 --> 00:56:51,554
If you need this…

727
00:56:56,768 --> 00:56:57,685
That's okay.

728
00:57:31,886 --> 00:57:33,054
They're all in.

729
00:57:40,186 --> 00:57:41,354
HAESEONG POLICE STATION

730
00:58:14,220 --> 00:58:15,513
Why did you bring this?

731
00:59:08,566 --> 00:59:09,442
What?

732
00:59:35,885 --> 00:59:37,303
Brother Hyeong-rok.

733
00:59:38,262 --> 00:59:39,639
Brother Su-hyeok!

734
00:59:41,891 --> 00:59:44,560
Come on out already.
I really hate this kind of thing.

735
00:59:50,149 --> 00:59:51,693
I love you. C'mere.

736
00:59:57,323 --> 00:59:59,534
Actually, I don't. So piss off!

737
01:00:01,119 --> 01:00:02,495
Sorry.

738
01:00:10,878 --> 01:00:14,674
I won't bother mentioning that this is
all thanks to my flypaper hands.

739
01:00:15,425 --> 01:00:17,552
Master, which way do we go now?

740
01:00:19,137 --> 01:00:20,304
Hold on a second.

741
01:00:23,057 --> 01:00:24,559
There's a door here.

742
01:00:25,810 --> 01:00:26,686
Come here.

743
01:00:27,395 --> 01:00:28,855
We can just open it.

744
01:00:34,902 --> 01:00:36,362
What is it?

745
01:00:36,863 --> 01:00:37,864
I can't see a thing.

746
01:00:49,542 --> 01:00:50,626
Hello, sirs.

747
01:00:52,545 --> 01:00:55,798
Why haven't you disbanded them yet?
Even the police are here.

748
01:00:56,299 --> 01:00:58,342
We did send some officers--

749
01:00:59,010 --> 01:01:00,470
OUTDOOR ASSEMBLY PERMIT FORM

750
01:01:01,512 --> 01:01:04,098
"They're exercising
their right and freedom to assemble."

751
01:01:04,599 --> 01:01:05,767
Explain it like that.

752
01:01:10,313 --> 01:01:13,357
After all the money
they gobbled up from us?

753
01:01:18,488 --> 01:01:19,322
What is it?

754
01:01:21,199 --> 01:01:23,701
We have intruders.

755
01:01:26,871 --> 01:01:29,707
-Cultists, begone!
-Begone!

756
01:01:30,291 --> 01:01:32,418
Pal-ho!

757
01:01:57,401 --> 01:01:59,362
What's that old geezer

758
01:01:59,862 --> 01:02:01,906
doing over there?

759
01:02:02,615 --> 01:02:04,242
We'll be transplanting

760
01:02:04,867 --> 01:02:06,369
your heart into him.

761
01:02:11,415 --> 01:02:14,043
But you said I'd be saving the world.

762
01:02:16,003 --> 01:02:17,338
You said…

763
01:02:19,674 --> 01:02:21,717
that in exchange for my life,

764
01:02:22,468 --> 01:02:24,804
you could save countless others.

765
01:02:27,181 --> 01:02:28,432
But you're just

766
01:02:30,017 --> 01:02:32,103
giving it to that old man?

767
01:02:34,272 --> 01:02:36,399
No need to feel wronged, child.

768
01:02:36,899 --> 01:02:39,735
The only truths that exist in this world

769
01:02:40,444 --> 01:02:42,864
are unfair, unreasonable,

770
01:02:43,948 --> 01:02:46,033
and unpleasant ones.

771
01:02:47,076 --> 01:02:48,661
No.

772
01:02:49,579 --> 01:02:50,955
Still, this isn't

773
01:02:51,914 --> 01:02:53,875
what you told me earlier.

774
01:02:55,001 --> 01:02:57,420
Why should I die

775
01:02:58,004 --> 01:02:59,797
just to save that old man?

776
01:03:00,298 --> 01:03:01,132
Why?

777
01:03:01,632 --> 01:03:03,009
Because you

778
01:03:03,593 --> 01:03:05,094
are nothing.

779
01:03:12,810 --> 01:03:14,103
<i>Die.</i>

780
01:03:14,979 --> 01:03:16,814
Die…

781
01:03:18,482 --> 01:03:19,483
<i>Gladly.</i>

782
01:03:23,529 --> 01:03:24,780
<i>Gladly…</i>

783
01:03:27,658 --> 01:03:29,702
But I don't want to die.

784
01:03:35,416 --> 01:03:36,667
Why…

785
01:03:37,627 --> 01:03:40,212
Why am I nothing?

786
01:03:42,048 --> 01:03:43,424
I am

787
01:03:44,967 --> 01:03:46,177
my grandma's…

788
01:03:48,596 --> 01:03:51,223
<i>entire world.</i>

789
01:03:53,768 --> 01:03:55,102
And I'm Ro-bin's…

790
01:03:57,813 --> 01:04:01,484
<i>one and only friend.</i>

791
01:04:04,278 --> 01:04:06,113
And I'm Mr. Son's…

792
01:04:08,991 --> 01:04:11,285
<i>adrenaline kick.</i>

793
01:04:13,329 --> 01:04:14,747
And

794
01:04:16,457 --> 01:04:17,583
Master.

795
01:04:22,630 --> 01:04:24,715
<i>I'm Master's…</i>

796
01:04:40,481 --> 01:04:42,108
I'm Master's…

797
01:05:11,637 --> 01:05:13,431
I'm not wild about the idea, but you're

798
01:05:15,057 --> 01:05:15,933
on my side.

799
01:05:43,586 --> 01:05:44,587
Where is she?

800
01:05:44,670 --> 01:05:45,546
Is that her?

801
01:05:45,629 --> 01:05:47,173
Hey, is that white thing Chae-ni?

802
01:05:47,256 --> 01:05:48,466
Chae-ni!

803
01:05:48,966 --> 01:05:51,469
-Chae-ni!
-Eun Chae-ni!

804
01:05:52,053 --> 01:05:53,888
-Chae-ni.
-Oh no, what do we do?

805
01:05:53,971 --> 01:05:56,140
Chae-ni! Are you conscious or not?

806
01:05:56,223 --> 01:05:58,851
It's me, Mr. Son. Are you okay?

807
01:05:59,810 --> 01:06:00,728
-Chae-ni!
-Oh no!

808
01:06:01,312 --> 01:06:04,106
-Chae-ni!
-Get this damn thing out of my face.

809
01:06:06,067 --> 01:06:07,234
Have we untied her?

810
01:06:09,528 --> 01:06:10,946
Stop!

811
01:06:15,159 --> 01:06:16,327
What was that?

812
01:06:20,456 --> 01:06:21,332
Mr. Son, hurry!

813
01:06:21,415 --> 01:06:22,750
-What do we do?
-Hurry up!

814
01:06:22,833 --> 01:06:23,793
What's going on?

815
01:06:25,169 --> 01:06:27,755
What do we do? Give that to me. All right!

816
01:06:29,715 --> 01:06:31,425
Hello. Call me Moon Mi-hui.

817
01:06:41,102 --> 01:06:42,895
-Here!
-Ro-bin!

818
01:06:55,741 --> 01:06:57,243
You bastard!

819
01:07:14,135 --> 01:07:15,886
-Chae-ni, are you okay?
-You okay?

820
01:07:16,762 --> 01:07:19,390
Damn you, Lady Trainwreck!

821
01:07:19,473 --> 01:07:20,641
My eyes!

822
01:07:21,183 --> 01:07:22,852
I can't see!

823
01:07:33,112 --> 01:07:34,572
Hey, catch her!

824
01:08:26,540 --> 01:08:28,584
I guess you felt a little bad.

825
01:08:29,168 --> 01:08:30,878
I'm not saving you for your sake

826
01:08:31,670 --> 01:08:33,672
but for theirs.

827
01:08:37,092 --> 01:08:38,802
Because when you hold a grudge,

828
01:08:40,429 --> 01:08:41,639
you're persistent.

829
01:08:43,599 --> 01:08:46,060
Why don't you get out of my face, then?

830
01:08:46,143 --> 01:08:47,561
Before I really hold a grudge.

831
01:08:54,318 --> 01:08:55,152
No.

832
01:09:08,123 --> 01:09:10,542
Did she really poke my eyes out
or something?

833
01:09:11,043 --> 01:09:12,586
What am I seeing?

834
01:09:19,051 --> 01:09:20,386
You go, Ms. Eun Chae-ni.

835
01:09:21,804 --> 01:09:22,763
To a safe place.

836
01:09:42,825 --> 01:09:44,285
-Of course.
-Again.

837
01:09:45,619 --> 01:09:46,537
Of course.

838
01:09:55,212 --> 01:09:56,922
What… What's this?

839
01:10:05,472 --> 01:10:07,850
How could Lady Trainwreck
disappear all by herself?

840
01:10:07,933 --> 01:10:10,602
This is why they say
people bite the hands who feed

841
01:10:10,686 --> 01:10:12,563
or desert the friends who save you.

842
01:10:16,984 --> 01:10:20,446
Mr. Son. If you're scared,
just hurl insults at me from behind.

843
01:10:21,488 --> 01:10:22,781
You bastard, son of a bitch.

844
01:10:22,865 --> 01:10:26,118
You potato-looking sap
with your corduroy pants. That do it?

845
01:11:14,249 --> 01:11:17,669
<i>But you're nothing.</i>

846
01:11:18,629 --> 01:11:19,546
<i>No.</i>

847
01:11:20,422 --> 01:11:22,299
<i>It's not that I'm nothing.</i>

848
01:11:23,092 --> 01:11:25,594
<i>I just haven't done anything yet.</i>

849
01:14:55,929 --> 01:15:00,934
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi

